      "comment_id" : 49361902,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "No, <code>System.lineSeparator()</code> should be used when you deal with non-portable resources (that is, resources specific to the underlying operating system). It has a different value wether you are running Java on Windows (\\r\\n) or Unix (\\n). If you use <code>System.lineSeparator()</code> all the time, you will therefore produce non portable files."
